In a std::multiset, if you pass a value directly to .erase(), C++ will destroy every single copy of that value in the entire set.
If your array had three pairs that all started with the number 10, xs.erase(10) instantly deletes all three of them!
when you do xs.insert(x) at the end of the loop, it only puts one 10 back. You have silently corrupted the state of your array.
